\n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                    \n                        \n                                    \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSoccer fans who are T-Mobile subscribers should be happy to hear about the newest perk from the company.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"subscribers-can-nab-mls-season-pass-for-free\"\u003e\n                        Subscribers Can Nab MLS Season Pass for Free\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eStarting on February 18, 2025, T-Mobile and Metro by T-Mobile postpaid subscribers can nab an MLS Season Pass for free. That’s a $99 value.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWith the subscription, you can see all live regular-season matches, MLS Cup playoff matches, Leagues Cup, and other programming and content with no blackouts. The league starts play on February 22, 2025.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eTo claim the perk, you can head to the T-Life app for \u003ca href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/t-life/id1111876388\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eiOS\u003c/a\u003e or \u003ca href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/7251228/type/dlg/sid/UUmuoUeUpU2035595/https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.tmobile.tuesdays\u0026amp;hl=en_US\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eAndroid\u003c/a\u003e. You can claim the free subscription until March 4, 2025.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eSince MLS Season Pass is available on Apple TV, you will need to have an Apple Account with a payment method on file. At the end of the 2025 MLS Season, the subscription automatically renews for the 2026 season for $99. So if you don’t want to pay, you will need to cancel one day before the renewal date.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eYou can access all the MLS action with the Apple TV app. It’s available on Apple devices, many smart TVs, streaming devices, and elsewhere. \u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eIf you’re not a soccer fan, T-Mobile has a variety of other perks for subscribers, like free in-flight Wi-Fi and high-speed data access outside the United States. Metro Flex Plus customers can also receive an Amazon Prime membership for free.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eT-Mobile hopes that perks like the MLS Season Pass can draw new subscribers and keep existing customers. If you’re in the market for a carrier, take a look at our \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/best-mobile-carrier/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecomparison of Verizon, AT\u0026amp;T, and T-Mobile\u003c/a\u003e to help you make the best decision.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"giving-more-users-a-taste-of-apple-tv\"\u003e\n                        Giving More Users a Taste of Apple TV\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEven though MLS isn’t as popular as other major sports leagues in the United States, the arrival of Lionel Messi has increased interest.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe free perk for T-Mobile subscribers looks to be a win for soccer fans and Apple, giving even more viewers a look at Apple’s streaming app when watching MLS action. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
